This paper deals with the task of dialogue emotion classification using various machine learning techniques. The most relevant sub-category for this task is likely to be "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) as it involves natural language processing and understanding. Other likely sub-categories include "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) and "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) as the paper uses various machine learning models for classification. "cs.SD" (Sound) could also be a possible sub-category as the paper deals with dialogue, which involves sound. Finally, "cs.CY" (Computers and Society) could be a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the potential applications of emotion detection in dialogue for various social scenarios.
